      },
      "lineNbr": 1417,
      "author": {
        "id": 1076138
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-04-25T13:56:59Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We can do that, but bear in mind that the ambient set starts at 0:\n\nCapInh:\t0000000000000000\nCapPrm:\t0000001fffffffff\nCapEff:\t0000001fffffffff\nCapBnd:\t0000001fffffffff\nCapAmb:\t0000000000000000\n\nAnd that you can only add to ambient if you have it in inh+prm. And you start with an empty inh.\n\nSo this would be mostly if the process has gained some caps before using Minijail. Usually doesn\u0027t happen, but better be safe.",
      "parentUuid": "39b90751_e395e88b",
      "revId": "8923285269f03a7f76b97e48c4f50d97d9bdfec2",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": true
